<HEADLINE>
WEATHER CAUSING PROBLEMS IN MALIBU
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By LEE BARNATHAN  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   MALIBU, Calif. _ The NCAA women's tennis championships logo
includes an ocean wave and a sandy beach, but what stands out is
the bright yellow tennis ball shaped like the sun.
</P>
<P>
   Around Pepperdine these days, the logo seems misguided. Someone
forgot to include the mist cloud which is over everything.
</P>
<P>
   For the second consecutive day, the early-morning marine layer
led to misty conditions that delayed the start of play. Tuesday,
there were supposed to be two rounds of singles matches, but the
weather pushed that back to Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   When the same conditions prevailed Wednesday, tournament
officials had no choice but to delay the start, then play both
rounds.
</P>
<P>
   The third round of singles, which was supposed to start at 10
a.m. PDT, began around noon. The quarterfinals, supposed to start
at 1:30 p.m., didn't start until between 3:10 and 4 p.m. Then
another round of mist delayed three quarterfinals unt97u
</P>
