   EDITORS:
</P>
<P>
   The nightly summaries of all slugs from  &UR; The New York Times News
Service &LR; , which move between 3 a.m. and 5 a.m. as the final
elements of our report, have been discontinued for the time being.
</P>
<P>
   The summaries, labeled BC-(category)-SLUGLIST-CLOSER, are a
casualty of a computer upgrade under way at The New York Times. New
software being installed by the newspaper makes the sub-program
that compiles the SLUGLISTS obsolete.
</P>
<P>
   Programming can be devised to reinstate the SLUGLISTS, but it
will take a few weeks. In the meantime, it would be useful to know
the level of interest in this element of our service.
</P>
<P>
   Editors who use the SLUGLISTS are invited to send their comments
on how they use the lists and how important they are. Comments
should be sent to:
</P>
<P>
   By e-mail:
</P>
<P>
   lmpaul(at)nytimes.com
</P>
<P>
   or, by land mail:
</P>
<P>
   Laurence M. Paul
</P>
<P>
   Executive Editor
</P>
