<P>
   COXNET BOOKS 0523 -- In Hamilton Jordan's new book, ``No Such
Thing as a Bad Day,'' the architect of Jimmy Carter's improbable
nomination for the presidency tells how quickly power and position
fade to irrelevance and how one's sense of proportion can change
between his 30s and his 50s. (Skube, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
Art includes a 3-column color photo of Hamilton Jordan and a 6-pica
color photo of the book jacket.
</P>
