<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FIZZY GUY WAS ALKA-SELTZER MASCOT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   QUESTION: What was the name of Alka-Seltzer's mascot?
</P>
<P>
   _ M.V., Hurst, Texas &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ANSWER: The tablet-bodied boy was originally known as Sparky,
but renamed Speedy for a ``speedy relief'' advertising campaign in
the 1950s, according to a corporate history of the character
published at www.alka-seltzer.com.
</P>
<P>
   ``Speedy appeared until the mid-'70s, when he was replaced by a
series of award-winning ads including `Man vs. Stomach,''' Warren
Dotz and Jim Morton write in ``What a Character!,'' a book about
advertising icons. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Radio actor Dick Beals, the voice of Speedy, is selling
autographed copies of his autobiography, ``Think Big,'' for $12. To
order, write to Beals at 1741 David Drived, Escondido, CA 92026. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Q: When did former Texas Rangers Julio Franco, Ruben Sierra and
Steve Buechele stop playing major-league baseball?
</P>
<P>
   _ E.M.T., Arlington, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Two of the players, Franco and Sierra, are still pursuing pro
careers.
</P>
<P>
   On May 2, Sierra signed a minor-league contract with the Rangers
and was assigned to the Triple A Oklahoma Redhawks. He was hitting
.370 with two homers and six RBIs through his first six games. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The 34-year-old outfielder's last full season in the majors was
in 1996, for the New York Yankees and Detroit Tigers, though he
played in 67 games for three other teams from 1997 to 1998.
</P>
<P>
   Franco, 41, had one at-bat for the Tampa Bay Devil Rays in 1999,
and last played a full season in 1997 for the Cleveland Indians and
Milwaukee Brewers. He's playing in Korea this year for the Samsung
Lions.
</P>
<P>
   Buechele, 38, played 11 seasons and ended his career in 1995,
returning to Texas for nine games after being released by the
Chicago Cubs.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Who plays the Australian military officer Brumby on ``JAG''?
</P>
<P>
   _ A.W.W., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: Lt. Cmdr. Mic Brumby, a foreign exchange officer with the
Royal Australian Navy, is played by Trevor Goddard.
</P>
<P>
   Goddard, 34, is a native of Perth, Australia, who was a
professional boxer before he took up acting. ``It's easier than
getting knocked about,'' he told AAP General News.
</P>
<P>
   He has also appeared in the films ``Mortal Kombat,'' ``Assault
on Devil's Island'' and ``Men.'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Write to any ``JAG'' cast member in care of ``JAG,'' Paramount
Studios, 5555 Melrose Ave., Bow Bldg., 2nd Floor, Hollywood, CA
90038.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
