from the Seattle Children's Festival to a women's prison here. By
Sam Howe Verhovek.
</P>
<P>
   NY-SUBWAY-NOISE (New York) _ Over the last 20 years, the New
York City subway system has slowly shed many of the worst
adjectives it picked up in the 1960s and 1970s: filthy, dangerous,
unreliable. But as more and more New Yorkers are venturing back to
the subway, they are still being greeted by at least one nasty
acquaintance from the old days: The Screech. By Randy Kennedy.
</P>
