bankruptcy bill. By Stephen Labaton.
</P>
<P>
   TOSHIBA-CHINA (Shanghai) _ Toshiba's multibillion dollar
settlement of class-action lawsuit in the United States last year
over defective laptops has backfired in China, where consumers are
charging that the Japanese company is discriminating against them
by not offering the same deal in China. The reaction shows the
underlying resentment of Japan that pervades China, where
commercial disputes can easily flare into nationalist bickering. By
Craig S. Smith.
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-ECONOMIC-DATA (Tokyo) _ The Japanese government says it
will correct its deliberate omission of data in its revision of its
statistics on economic growth for the fourth quarter of last year
when it releases new economic figures on June 10. By Stephanie
Strom.
