it is the trial that should be, one that puts top honchos Bill
Gates and Steve Ballmer on the witness stand to show why a
corporate breakup fails to fit its purported antitrust crimes and
would likely not only ruin its business but also set back the New
Economy. For Microsoft critics, it was the trial that should have
been, the moment missed when Gates instead came across in the
courtroom on videotape as an ignorant lout. But for judge who tried
