<P>
   CHINA-TRADE (Washington) _ Folo on the House passage of the
China trade bill and a look forward at possible difficulties in the
Senate. By Eric Schmitt.
</P>
<P>
   LEBANON (Beirut, Lebanon) _ As the Israeli troop withdrawal
settled into a reality, the Lebanese proudly celebrated a new
national holiday, Resistance Day, with a jubilant rally at the now
empty Khiam prison, which is notorious here for the alleged torture
of occupation fighters by Israel's South Lebanese militia allies.
By Deborah Sontag.
</P>
<P>
   PERU-POLITICS (Lima, Peru) _ President Alberto Fujimori has
strongly hinted that Peru will postpone Sunday's presidential
runoff election in order to satisfy critics of the election
process. By Clifford Krauss.
