<HEADER>
A5670 &Cx1f; tad-z
r l BC-FASHION-ROWLEY28-COX     05-25 0373
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FASHION-ROWLEY28-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    A style chat with designer Cynthia Rowley
 &HT;    Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, May 28.
 &HT;    By A. Scott Walton
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Since she has ``no money for advertising,'' designer
Cynthia Rowley does whatever she can to be noticed. She took
someone's ``bad advice'' and appeared in a deodorant commercial.
She does free promos for E!'s new cable fashion channel and
co-wrote a rather flippant lifestyle book called ``Swell.'' She
even spent the recent eve of her daughter Kitt's first birthday in
Atlanta _ signing the book and appearing at Bauder College's annual
senior design competition.
</P>
<P>
   In a chat with fashion editor A. Scott Walton, Rowley came
across as someone who maintains her sense of humor while enduring
the necessary evils of seeking fame in her field. Q: What's your
stance on e-commerce and Web sites?
</P>
<P>
   A: ``I'm working on one that would have really crazy things; not
clothes necessarily, but, like, my inventions. (For instance) the
Baby Mop, which is like, a little suit and gloves they could crawl
all over the floor in. And the Hands Free Baby Feeder, which is
based on the beer can hats. And the toothbrush for lovers, which is
really just a pink toothbrush and a blue one superglued together,
but we don't have to tell people that, do we?
</P>
<P>
   Q: More and more, designing for lifestyles is what it's all
about, right?
</P>
<P>
   A: Yeah, I wanna do, like, scooters and, like, tools for girls.
Wouldn't that be cute? Pink tools? Maybe I shouldn't be letting the
cat out of the bag. ...
</P>
<P>
   Q: What do you wear when you don't know what to wear?
</P>
<P>
   A: My leather pants. Everybody calls me Jim Morrison because I
wear them all the time. I can dress 'em up or dress 'em down,
whatever. And really sexy shoes, because no matter what you wear
with them you usually look good and feel good, too.'' Q: What are
``Swell'' qualities in a guy?
</P>
<P>
   A: Let's see ... a sense of humor ... smart ... old-fashioned,
in a way ... and I guess a really cute butt.
</P>
<P>
   Rowley's designs are sold at Peke and Saks Fifth Avenue.
</P>
<P>
   A. Scott Walton writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
