   Separate budgets move daily with spot news, features, sports and
commentary.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   DOW _ The Dow was down more than 200 points at 10,327 around 3
p.m. Microsoft dragged heavily on the blue-chip index after a
federal judge signaled that the government's proposal to break up
the company may not go far enough. The Nasdaq was down 16.06 at
3,254.55. (Walker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   GATEWAY-IXL _ Gateway Inc., the No. 2 direct seller of personal
computers, agreed to buy a 10 percent stake in Consumer Financial
Network, a unit of IXL Enterprises Inc., for $150 million to
broaden Internet-related business. (Katz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
