   ATTACK _ HAPEVILLE, Ga. _ The small town of Hapeville has never
seen the likes of this. Early Thursday a woman was raped and bound
and someone used a box cutter to carve a racial slur into her
stomach. (Longa, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   GLUE _ When 6-year-old Kailey Browning of Lilburn caught a
falling cactus that left more than 100 hard-to-see spines in her
arms, a Gwinnett County ER doc decided to try a new procedure to
remove them. Earlier this week, he poured Elmer's glue on Kailey's
arms, dried it with heat lamp and peeled away the little girl's
pain. Kailey's mom laughed when she first heard the idea, but now
she's a believer. The ER doctor learned about the procedure from an
Atlanta colleague who had just happened to hear about it during a
conference this month. (Stanford, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
