<P>
   POLITICAL NEWS (``p'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-TEXAS-GOP (Austin, Texas) _ George W. Bush was denied a
governor's traditional role as chairman of the state delegation to
the Republican National Convention four years ago by the socially
conservative Texas Republican Convention. Now, as the party's
apparent presidential nominee, he has no plans to attend this
year's state convention in Houston. Bush spokesman Karen Hughes
says the governor likely will be campaigning in another state
during the Texas meeting. By CLAY ROBISON and R. G. RATCLIFFE.
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-POWELL (Austin, Texas) _ In a well-choreographed setting,
Texas Gov. George W. Bush holds back-to-back meetings with South
African President Thabo Mbeki and retired Army Gen. Colin Powell.
Powell says he is not interested in being Bush's running mate, but
would consider a job in a Bush White House. By PEGGY FIKAC.
(Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   GORE-TENN (Nashville, Tenn.) _ Campaigning in his home state of
Tennessee, Vice President Al Gore proposes tax breaks to help
working families who need after-school child care. By BENNETT ROTH.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   SECURITY-BREACH (Washington) _ Attorney General Janet Reno,
stunned that undercover agents using fake cards identifying them as
law officers were able to penetrate 19 federal buildings, promises
to revamp her department's security system. That means guards will
stop giving preferential treatment to fellow law officers. We check
other federal agencies where security was breached. By MARK HELM.
(Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   FUNDING-LOOPHOLE (Washington) _ The House will vote today on
whether to take a step toward closing the so-called ``527
loophole'' that allows political groups to raise and spend money
without identifying the financial supporters. By GREG McDONALD.
</P>
