   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ The trouble with determining the
appropriate legal consequences of Bill Clinton's misdeeds is that
no one is neutral toward him. After an Arkansas panel recommended
the harshest penalty it could _ disbarment _ one of the
participants insisted that the group ``approached this as we would
any other lawyer.'' Sure. And cows can fly. Clinton isn't just any
other lawyer, and there's not a soul in Arkansas that doesn't love
him or loathe him. By MARIANNE MEANS. (Already filed.)
</P>
