   For Sunday:
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MILITARY-DEATH-PENALTY (Washington) _ For the first time in
nearly 40 years, the U.S. military is preparing to execute one of
its own, an Army private convicted in 1989 of murdering two taxi
drivers in Killeen, Texas. Not much stands between Dwight Loving,
34, of Rochester, N.Y., and lethal injection at the Fort
Leavenworth, Kan., federal penitentiary _ except President Clinton
and what his lawyers and other legal experts complain is a vague
and unfair bureaucratic process now under way in the Army. By ERIC
ROSENBERG. (Already filed.)
</P>
