<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-25 20:33 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5859 &Cx1f; ttc-z
u v BC-LADN-BUDGET &LR;      05-25 0319
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs on
Friday, May 26, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Dennis Liff at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   HMO-SUIT (Los Angeles) _ The California Medical Association,
which represents 30,000 physicians statewide, filed a lawsuit
Thursday in federal court against PacifiCare, WellPoint Health
Networks, its subsidiary Blue Cross of California and HealthNet.
The suit, which seeks class-action status, alleges the managed care
companies pay rates for services that don't cover their costs, do
not pay medical bills in a timely manner and unlawfully deny or
delay treatment. By Jason Takenouchi and Chris Sieroty. (Will move
in the ``a'' national news and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   MAHONY-EXECUTIONS (Los Angeles) _ Cardinal Roger Mahony,
archbishop of Los Angeles, called Thursday for California Gov. Gray
Davis to halt all executions. Mahony made the statement at a press
conference in Washington, D.C., where the religious leader was
attending a national meeting on social issues hosted by the U.S.
Catholic Conference, the organization of America's Roman Catholic
bishops. By Bill Hillburg. (Will move in the ``a'' national news
and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   LAUSD-ROMER (Los Angeles) _ Former Colorado Gov. Roy Romer is
one of three finalists for superintendent of the Los Angeles
Unified School District, officials said Thursday. The school board
interviewed Romer on Thursday and planned to interview the
remaining two candidates Friday and Tuesday. Board President
Genethia Hayes would not reveal the names or occupations of the
remaining candidates but said they are actively seeking the job. By
David R. Baker. (Will move in the ``a'' national news and ``n''
California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
