<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-IRAQ-U.N.-NYT (moved on Wednesday, May 24)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, May 24,
about the new United Nations commission for inspecting Iraqi
weapons referred incorrectly to the unit being formed by the
commission's chairman, Hans Blix. It is the inspection commission;
his advisory panel already exists.
</P>
<P>
   BC-GORE-SOCSEC-NYT (moved on Wednesday, May 24)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, May 24,
about Vice President Al Gore's position on Social Security
misstated one element of his personal finances. Gore receives no
income from investments in the stock market. Although his financial
disclosure form lists dividend income, the stock is held in trust
for his mother, and the income goes only to her.
