   (NYT40) NEW YORK -- May 25, 2000 -- MERRILL-LYNCH -- Stanley
O'Neal, head of Merrill Lynch's 14,200 brokers, selected a
marketing executive as his deputy. O'Neal, the first person not a
stockbroker to run the nation's largest brokerage network, has
named another non-broker, James Gorman, to be the No. 2 executive,
people inside the firm said. He also moved a few executives out of
top jobs and promoted several others as part of a reorganization of
the unit, those people said. (Ruby Washington/The New York Times)
