BIZ-BOOK-B&AMP;W -- Dennis N.T. Perkins' new book, ``Leading at the
Edge: Leadership Lessons from the Extraordinary Saga of
Shackleton's Antarctic Expedition,'' explores the outer limits of
human endurance and their connection to the entrepeneurial spirit.
Sir Ernest Shackleton and his expedition team were stranded for
more than 600 days in Antarctica after their ship became icebound.
(The New York Times)
</P>
