<P>
   (NYT14) MT. DORA, Fla. -- May 25, 2000 -- ANTIQUES-COLUMN -- A
19-foot Chris-Craft Racing Runabout made in 1951. It is one of the
most popular classic boats in the United States, according to
Wilson W. Wright, the executive director of the Chris-Craft Antique
Boat Club, which is based in Tallahassee, Fla. From 1947 to July
1954, 503 were built. ``They were the Corvettes, the Thunderbirds
of their era,'' he said. (Chris-Craft Antique Boat Club/The New
York Times)
