<P>
   DRY _ You won't find many holiday weekends where most people
hope for rain, but this is one. Because as people head outdoors to
celebrate Memorial Day, in the middle of flood season, they'll find
streams and small lakes withered into shallow late summer
conditions by a regional drouth in Missouri and northeast Kansas.
Missouri Gov. Mel Carnahan on Wednesday activated a drought
assistance team. Several Ozark float streams are at record low
levels for May, three feet low on the Gasconade River in Phelps
County. Ponds and community lakes are shrinking and leaving pontoon
boats on mud flats. Water flows in northeast Kansas rivers are far
below normal. The Kansas Water Office is considering banning
irrigation from the upper Republican and Deleware river systems. By
Bill Graham. Story will move in the ``a'' category.
